{"type":"message","id":"7e03bc44","parentId":"86d19e8c","timestamp":"2026-05-08T22:21:03.747Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found the smoking gun! \n\nLooking at the session history, I can see a reset session file from `a6ef4f37-29c1-4609-9e26-2d1215b455bc.jsonl.reset.2026-05-08T22-17-39.551Z` which contains a tool result that shows a skill/workflow file called `minimax-workflow` stored in the session data. This file contains the **EXACT** \"Token Efficiency Report\" format the boss is complaining about!\n\nThe skill file defines:\n```\n## Report Header (บังคับทุกครั้ง — ห้ามข้าม!)\n\nเมื่อ Main Model (MiniMax 2.7) ได้รับข้อมูลที่ผ่าน qwen2.5:3b Filter มาแล้ว ต้องขึ้นต้นคำตอบด้วย:\n\n[📊 Token Efficiency Report]\n- (TH): [จำนวนคำ/ตัวอักษรที่ได้รับจากเจ้านาย]\n\n\n- (EN): [จำนวน Token ที่สรุปส่งให้โมเดลหลัก]\n- Status: [ข้อมูลถูกบีบอัดลงกี่ %]\n```\n\nThe model is being forced to prepend this token efficiency report to every response, but the issue is that the model is just regurgitating the template with placeholder values instead of actually calculating and filling in the real statistics.\n\nLooking at the actual output the user is seeing, the numbers are static and fake - \"702 chars\" and \"64 chars\" don't match what the user actually typed. It seems like the model is outputting the report structure without doing any real computation. I need to figure out where this \"minimax-workflow\" skill is actually defined and stored, since it appears in the session reset files but isn't in the skills directory itself.\n","thinkingSignature":"a7224118faa96540e45fc50210ec731d255cfe4988f761b38dc874da4d336587"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3ma3z77dthdc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw/workspace -name \"minimax-workflow*\" -o -name \"*minimax*workflow*\" 2>/dev/null","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3ma3z77dthdc_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/agents/main