g configuration, I'd need to introduce a `streaming:` subkey under `telegram:` with the `mode: partial` and preview settings. This is a structural change to the existing config format.\n\nGiven the complexity of properly implementing this change, I think the user needs to provide more context about whether they're proposing a config format change or if this is meant to work with the existing structure. I should ask for clarification before proceeding with the modification.\n\nHowever, to actually address the user's underlying issue with the Token Efficiency Report, the priority is to remove or rename the minimax-workflow skill that's causing the spam. I'll focus on that first since it's the root cause of the problem.\n","thinkingSignature":"86dbf01d31a3a97d3f18ebad696f243517fc19af2e7158f433a5b555ab5a23a7"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nทำทั้งสองอย่างเลยครับ!\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jwq4wa8ltcaq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mv /home/apinan/.hermes/skills/protocol/minimax-workflow/SKILL.md /home/apinan/.hermes/skills/protocol/minimax-workflow/SKILL.md.bak 2>/dev/null && echo \"Disabled minimax-workflow skill\"","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jwq4wa8ltcaq_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.hermes/config.yaml | grep -n \"streaming\\|display:\" | head -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7405,"output":702,"cacheRead":68800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76907,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778278936593,"responseId":"064d951ab491a6f03cba3f55474241d0"}}
