{"type":"message","id":"25be353b","parentId":"760bbd94","timestamp":"2026-05-08T22:58:12.763Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clearer picture. Let me summarize:\n\n**Hermes Status: RUNNING ✅** (after the restart at 05:56:39)\n\n**Issues found:**\n\n1. **MCP JSONRPC parse errors** — An MCP server is emitting non-JSON output (ANSI escape codes visible in the error: `\\x1b[2m2026-05-08T22:56:...`) on stdout, which breaks the JSONRPC stdio protocol. This caused the old Hermes process to crash with exit code 75/TEMPFAIL and restart.\n\n2. **Failed MCP servers** (non-critical, just warnings):\n   - `brave` - failed to connect\n   - `opencode-enforce-context-mode` - failed to connect\n   - `comfyui-mcp` - failed to connect\n\n3. **Working MCP servers** (from current process list):\n   - socraticode, puppeteer, filesystem, sequential-thinking, memory, exa, context7-mcp, mcp-debugger, mcp-server-terminal, server-everything, zapier-sdk, comfyui-mcp\n\n4. **Pre-filter still active**: The gateway logs show \"Gateway local pre-filter applied\" — the pre-filter script is still running. This is the \"qwen2.5:3b Ultra-Compressed\" filter we saw earlier in the logs.\n\n5. **Streaming is now enabled** for Telegram, but it was previously `false` so the old crashed instance at 05:25 had streaming disabled.\n\nThe restart happened successfully and Hermes is back online. I should report this status to the user.\n","thinkingSignature":"3ee5d175a41dc6005070b689917b27c4f2268cd3e7376208ce813255af5d0844"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n## 🧑🏼‍💻 Hermes Status — สถานะหลัง restart\n\n---\n\n### ✅ **Hermes กลับมาทำงานแล้วครับ**\n\n| Item | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| Service | ✅ `active (running)` ตั้งแต่ 05:56:39 |\n| PID | 2521801 |\n| Memory | 1.8G (peak: 2.0G) |\n| Tasks | 257 |\n| Uptime | ~1 นาที |\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ ปัญหาที่พบ (ไม่ critical แต่ควรรู้)\n\n**1. MCP JSONRPC Parse Error — ทำให้ restart**\n```\nFailed to parse JSONRPC message from server\nInvalid JSON: '\\x1b[2m2026-05-08T22:56:...'\n```\n→ MCP server ตัวหนึ่ง emit ANSI escape codes ออกมาแทน JSON ทำให้ Hermes crash (exit 75) แล้ว restart อัตโนมัติ\n\n**2. MCP servers ที่ fail (warning ไม่ทำให้ระบบล่ม):**\n- `brave` — ไม่พร้อมใช้งาน\n- `opencode-enforce-context-mode` — ไม่พร้อม\n- `comfyui-mcp` — ไม่พร้อม\n\n**3. Pre-filter ยังทำงานอยู่** — เห็น log `\"Gateway local pre-filter applied\"` อยู่ แต่ไม่ได้ทำให้ crash\n\n---\n\n### 🔧 สิ่งที่รันอยู่ตอนนี้ (MCP ที่ใช้ได้)\n\n| MCP Server | Status |\n|------------|--------|\n| socraticode | ✅ |\n| puppeteer | ✅ |\n| filesystem | ✅ |\n| sequential-thinking | ✅ |\n| memory | ✅ |\n| exa | ✅ |\n| context7-mcp | ✅ |\n| mcp-debugger | ✅ |\n| mcp-server-terminal | ✅ |\n| server-everything | ✅ |\n| zapier-sdk | ✅ |\n\n---\n\n**สรุป:** Hermes รันปกติดี ปัญหา crash เกิดจาก MCP server ตัวหนึ่งส่งข้อมูลผิด format แต่ระบบ auto-restart จัดการได้แล้ว 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2282,"output":967,"cacheRead":84032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87281,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778281078541,"responseId":"064d9d78ef944bcdaf952551e88c81c0"}}
