{"type":"message","id":"5fe4955e","parentId":"24df69ba","timestamp":"2026-05-08T22:58:48.936Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full timeline clearly. Let me trace the restart chain:\n\n1. **05:22:56** - User ran `systemctl --user restart hermes-gateway` (from our earlier command)\n2. **05:22:56** - Hermes started shutting down. During shutdown, it tried to clean up MCP servers but one of them (brave?) emitted ANSI escape codes into the JSONRPC stream\n3. **05:23:01** - JSONRPC parse error during shutdown cleanup → Hermes exits with code 1 (not 75, just a regular failure)\n4. **05:23:06** - systemd immediately restarts Hermes (startup after failure)\n\n\n5. **05:25:13** - New Hermes instance (2494375) begins connecting to MCP servers, but `opencode-enforce-context-mode`, `comfyui-mcp`, and `brave` all fail after 3 attempts each\n6. **05:25:36** - Despite the MCP failures, Hermes finishes initialization\n7. **05:56:30** - A second JSONRPC parse error occurs, this time with exit code 75, triggering another restart\n8. **05:56:39** - Hermes comes back up and stabilizes\n\nSo the slowness stems from MCP servers timing out on their initial connections, plus the JSONRPC parse errors causing two separate restarts. The exit code 75 indicates a TEMPFAIL, which likely means systemd's restart delay kicked in between the crash at 05:56:30 and the successful startup at 05:56:39.\n","thinkingSignature":"ed8f2988b100399939089160e0e4468446465b2b9997ced92bbbe3cd3cf2261e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_juz3qtspoh0k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.config/systemd/user/hermes-gateway.service.d/override.conf 2>/dev/null","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_juz3qtspoh0k_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"systemctl --user show hermes-gateway.service -p RestartUSec,RestartAttempts,NRestarts 2>/dev/null","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3194,"output":441,"cacheRead":87872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91507,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778281118596,"responseId":"064d9da0c0530ff9e3adecb15ed756e3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d64d81d4","parentId":"5fe4955e","timestamp":"2026-05-08T22:58:48.975Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_juz3qtspoh0k_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Service]\n# Keep Telegram downtime short after crashes/restarts.\nRestartSec=5\nRestartSteps=0\nRestartMaxDelaySec=5\n\n# SocratiCode MCP sometimes leaves npm/node children behind on gateway restart.\n# Clean them so the next gateway start does not spawn duplicates or hang shutdown.\nExecStopPost=/home/apinan/.hermes/bin/cleanup-socraticode.sh\nTimeoutStopSec=45"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"[Service]\n# Keep Telegram downtime short after crashes/restarts.\nRestartSec=5\nRestartSteps=0\nRestartMaxDelaySec=5\n\n# SocratiCode MCP sometimes leaves npm/node children behind on gateway restart.\n# Clean them so the next gateway start does not spawn duplicates or hang shutdown.\nExecStopPost=/home/apinan/.hermes/bin/cleanup-socraticode.sh\nTimeoutStopSec=45","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778281128975}}
