{"type":"message","id":"17b4e44d","parentId":"6f751eb4","timestamp":"2026-05-08T23:00:58.738Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still crashing! The crash is happening too fast (06:00:37, before even 1 minute), so the problem isn't those MCP servers I commented out. The ANSI escape sequence issue is coming from somewhere else.\n\nThe error shows `\\x1b[2m2026-05-08T23:00:...` - so it's happening at 23:00 timestamp in the payload from some MCP server.\n\nLet me check which MCP server has the pre-filter/local_qwen stuff - that `local_qwen_gateway_filter.log` was mentioned earlier. And let me look at what's running that could emit ANSI codes.\n\nThe crash happens almost immediately after startup, which means it's one of the primary MCP servers, not the optional ones I disabled.\n\n\nI need to find where that ANSI output is actually coming from before the gateway crashes.\n","thinkingSignature":"8290cdbda62f8f9f3537debde62c62c9fb22fb25c9a5f53ed889b6ca03c763bb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1mckdksezbvz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sleep 10 && journalctl --user -u hermes-gateway -n 40 --no-pager 2>&1 | tail -25","timeout":20}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1mckdksezbvz_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.hermes/logs/mcp-stderr.log 2>/dev/null && tail -20 ~/.hermes/logs/mcp-stderr.log 2>/dev/null","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":804,"output":297,"cacheRead":93696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94797,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778281249656,"responseId":"064d9e237e955ae768c7cf7a41522da7"}}
