{"type":"message","id":"f528399a","parentId":"c7277201","timestamp":"2026-05-08T23:01:18.611Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see from the mcp-stderr.log that the MCP servers are starting. The crash is happening at 06:00:37 which is BEFORE our restart at 06:00:42. Let me check the timeline more carefully.\n\nActually wait - the crash happened at 06:00:37 which is just a few seconds after our restart command at 06:00:42... no wait that's impossible because systemd shows the service stopped at 06:00:42. \n\nLet me think about this again:\n- We edited config at ~06:00:30\n- We ran `systemctl --user restart hermes-gateway` at ~06:00:35\n- The crash log shows 06:00:37 → the OLD gateway (started at 05:56:39) crashed at 06:00:37\n\n\n- The new gateway started at 06:00:42 but the timing doesn't add up\n\nActually, looking at the sequence: we restart at 06:00:42, yet the crash log is timestamped 06:00:37 - that's five seconds before the restart command even ran. So either the timestamps are off, or I'm misreading the sequence of events.\n\nLet me wait for the journalctl output to finish and see what the current state actually shows.\n","thinkingSignature":"ede902d158ddf04b495b544fd59d80d7393b9c7b34674379096cccf975db92a4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2wf0ut8yvpkq_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"glow-haven","timeout":15000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":546,"output":318,"cacheRead":94464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95328,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778281268768,"responseId":"064d9e382b17645ebc3a770704173f65"}}
