{"type":"message","id":"f36f2cf4","parentId":"6c9ad4d1","timestamp":"2026-05-08T23:02:07.247Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The crash happens RIGHT after restart (06:00:32 stopping, 06:00:37 crash). This happens during the shutdown phase when MCP servers are being killed, and one of them emits ANSI escape codes as it dies.\n\nThe pattern `\\x1b[2m2026-05-08T23:00:` appears right at the moment of shutdown. This suggests it's a process that's outputting terminal color codes during the shutdown sequence.\n\nLet me check if there are NPM/node processes running from the old gateway that are still outputting:\n\nFrom the shutdown diagnostic at 06:00:31:\n- zapier-sdk mcp (2521937) — still running!\n- comfyui-mcp (2521981) — still running!\n- mcp-server-terminal (2522134) — still running!\n\n\n- exa-mcp-server (2522135) — still running!\n- context7-mcp (2522340) — still running!\n- sequential-thinking (2522342) — still running!\n- puppeteer-mcp-server (2522378) — still running!\n- server-everything (2522379) — still running!\n- mcp-debugger (2522394) — still running!\n- mcp-server-memory (2522395) — still running!\n- mcp-server-filesystem (2522409) — still running!\n- puppeteer-mcp-server (2522666) — still running!\n\nThe shutdown diagnostic captures a moment where I'm iterating through processes still running during gateway termination. The crash at 06:00:37 coincides with one of these MCP servers emitting ANSI codes as it's forcibly killed. These orphaned processes from the previous gateway instance are the culprit — they're writing to stdout in terminal format rather than clean JSON, causing the crash when Hermes tries to parse their output.\n\nThe cleanup script specified in ExecStopPost isn't actually removing these leftover processes, which is why they're still present and interfering with the restart sequence.\n","thinkingSignature":"1dfdd78b3366f22742d384b456ddff4d0f6d41a1297e989fa6e273aae19bed0e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r2fsqkbzcqcq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.hermes/bin/cleanup-socraticode.sh 2>/dev/null","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r2fsqkbzcqcq_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.hermes/bin/ 2>/dev/null","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2076,"output":489,"cacheRead":96768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99333,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778281315244,"responseId":"064d9e644a9d96bbd1458c4eb2e8a1a2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"762a82e9","parentId":"f36f2cf4","timestamp":"2026-05-08T23:02:07.282Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r2fsqkbzcqcq_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -u\n\nPATTERN='npm exec socraticode|sh -c socraticode|node .*/socraticode($| )|node .*/node_modules/.bin/socraticode($| )'\n\npids=\"$(pgrep -u \"$USER\" -f \"$PATTERN\" || true)\"\nif [ -z \"$pids\" ]; then\n  exit 0\nfi\n\n# First try graceful termination.\nkill -TERM $pids 2>/dev/null || true\nsleep 2\n\n# Force-kill anything still alive.\npids=\"$(pgrep -u \"$USER\" -f \"$PATTERN\" || true)\"\nif [ -n \"$pids\" ]; then\n  kill -KILL $pids 2>/dev/null || true\nfi\n\nexit 0"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -u\n\nPATTERN='npm exec socraticode|sh -c socraticode|node .*/socraticode($| )|node .*/node_modules/.bin/socraticode($| )'\n\npids=\"$(pgrep -u \"$USER\" -f \"$PATTERN\" || true)\"\nif [ -z \"$pids\" ]; then\n  exit 0\nfi\n\n# First try graceful termination.\nkill -TERM $pids 2>/dev/null || true\nsleep 2\n\n# Force-kill anything still alive.\npids=\"$(pgrep -u \"$USER\" -f \"$PATTERN\" || true)\"\nif [ -n \"$pids\" ]; then\n  kill -KILL $pids 2>/dev/null || true\nfi\n\nexit 0","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778281327282}}
