{"type":"message","id":"a1871264","parentId":"a8cbe3f8","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:39:58.394Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! In `gateway/run.py` at line 6406-6416, the code already checks for `_bridge_done`:\n\n```python\n# Emit agent:start hook (minimax-bridge hook sets _bridge_done if message should go through bridge)\nawait self.hooks.emit(\"agent:start\", hook_ctx)\n\n# If bridge hook set _bridge_done → skip agent, return bridge result directly\nif hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_done\") and hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_result\"):\n```\n\nSo the code EXISTS. But the user says the agent doesn't recognize the flag. Let me look more closely at the code around line 6406-6416 to understand the full flow.\n","thinkingSignature":"929696d6227c2b812121d15bb5350e158c7bbacdedd22df9c4a620c5c3146c35"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7f1jgid0oec7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '6390,6440p' ~/.hermes/hermes-agent/gateway/run.py","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":503,"output":193,"cacheRead":116864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117560,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778319586396,"responseId":"064e33e453d56d6d2f7935630862ff43"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6350a68f","parentId":"a1871264","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:39:58.423Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7f1jgid0oec7_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"source=source,\n            history=history,\n        )\n        if message_text is None:\n            return\n\n        # Bind this gateway run generation to the adapter's active-session\n        # event so deferred post-delivery callbacks can be released by the\n        # same run that registered them.\n        self._bind_adapter_run_generation(\n            self.adapters.get(source.platform),\n            session_key,\n            run_generation,\n        )\n\n        try:\n            # Emit agent:start hook (minimax-bridge hook sets _bridge_done if message should go through bridge)\n            hook_ctx = {\n                \"platform\": source.platform.value if source.platform else \"\",\n                \"user_id\": source.user_id,\n                \"session_id\": session_entry.session_id,\n                \"message\": message_text[:500],\n            }\n            await self.hooks.emit(\"agent:start\", hook_ctx)\n\n            # If bridge hook set _bridge_done → skip agent, return bridge result directly\n            if hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_done\") and hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_result\"):\n                response = hook_ctx[\"_bridge_result\"]\n                agent_result = {\"final_response\": response, \"messages\": [], \"api_calls\": 0}\n            else:\n                # Run the agent normally\n                agent_result = await self._run_agent(\n                    message=message_text,\n                    context_prompt=context_prompt,\n                    history=history,\n                    source=source,\n                    session_id=session_entry.session_id,\n                    session_key=session_key,\n                    run_generation=run_generation,\n                    event_message_id=event.message_id,\n                    channel_prompt=event.channel_prompt,\n                )\n\n            # Stop persistent typing indicator now that the agent is done\n            try:\n                _typing_adapter = self.adapters.get(source.platform)\n                if _typing_adapter and hasattr(_typing_adapter, \"stop_typing\"):\n                    await _typing_adapter.stop_typing(source.chat_id)\n            except Exception:\n                pass"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18,"aggregated":"source=source,\n            history=history,\n        )\n        if message_text is None:\n            return\n\n        # Bind this gateway run generation to the adapter's active-session\n        # event so deferred post-delivery callbacks can be released by the\n        # same run that registered them.\n        self._bind_adapter_run_generation(\n            self.adapters.get(source.platform),\n            session_key,\n            run_generation,\n        )\n\n        try:\n            # Emit agent:start hook (minimax-bridge hook sets _bridge_done if message should go through bridge)\n            hook_ctx = {\n                \"platform\": source.platform.value if source.platform else \"\",\n                \"user_id\": source.user_id,\n                \"session_id\": session_entry.session_id,\n                \"message\": message_text[:500],\n            }\n            await self.hooks.emit(\"agent:start\", hook_ctx)\n\n            # If bridge hook set _bridge_done → skip agent, return bridge result directly\n            if hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_done\") and hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_result\"):\n                response = hook_ctx[\"_bridge_result\"]\n                agent_result = {\"final_response\": response, \"messages\": [], \"api_calls\": 0}\n            else:\n                # Run the agent normally\n                agent_result = await self._run_agent(\n                    message=message_text,\n                    context_prompt=context_prompt,\n                    history=history,\n                    source=source,\n                    session_id=session_entry.session_id,\n                    session_key=session_key,\n                    run_generation=run_generation,\n                    event_message_id=event.message_id,\n                    channel_prompt=event.channel_prompt,\n                )\n\n            # Stop persistent typing indicator now that the agent is done\n            try:\n                _typing_adapter = self.adapters.get(source.platform)\n                if _typing_adapter and hasattr(_typing_adapter, \"stop_typing\"):\n                    await _typing_adapter.stop_typing(source.chat_id)\n            except Exception:\n                pass","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778319598422}}
{"type":"message","id":"3f0876df","parentId":"6350a68f","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:40:41.608Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. Let me verify my understanding and summarize it clearly for the boss.\n\n**Current architecture:**\n\n1. **minimax-bridge hook** (`~/.hermes/hooks/minimax-bridge/handler.py`)\n   - Listens on `agent:start` event\n   - Runs `universal_bridge.py` on the message\n   - If bridge succeeds, sets `context[\"_bridge_done\"] = True` and `context[\"_bridge_result\"] = <result>`\n   - If bridge fails, does nothing\n\n2. **gateway/run.py** (lines 6406-6426)\n   - Emits `agent:start` hook with `hook_ctx`\n   - After hook runs, checks `hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_done\")` and `hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_result\")`\n   - If both are true → skips agent entirely, returns `_bridge_result` as final response\n   - If not → runs agent normally\n\nSo the bridge mechanism IS already wired into the gateway at the correct point. The hook injects `_bridge_done` and `_bridge_result` into `hook_ctx`, and the gateway checks them after the hook runs.\n\n**The question is: does the agent (when it runs normally) have access to `_bridge_done`?**\n\nLooking at the code flow:\n- When bridge fails (or is not applicable), `agent_result = await self._run_agent(...)` is called\n- The agent receives `message`, `history`, `context_prompt`, etc.\n- The `_bridge_done` flag is NOT passed to the agent — it's only used in the gateway to decide whether to skip agent entirely\n\nBut wait - when the bridge DOESN'T set `_bridge_done`, the agent runs normally. So the agent never sees `_bridge_done`. The boss says \"agent ยังไม่รู้จัก _bridge_done flag\" - which means when the bridge FAILS or doesn't run, the agent doesn't know about the bridge flag at all.\n \nThe gateway flow shows that when the bridge hook sets `_bridge_done` and `_bridge_result`, the gateway uses those directly and skips the agent entirely. So the hook is functioning at the gateway level, but the agent itself has no awareness of the flag. The gateway either uses the bridge result directly or runs the agent without any knowledge of the bridge attempt.\n","thinkingSignature":"68cf9ed9004f00bd6fc5e2a6c311df8ad8011194c907a522b29f29f50eb60a04"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n🧑🏼‍💻 **เช็คความเข้าใจแล้ว สรุปดังนี้:**\n\n---\n\n### ✅ สิ่งที่มีอยู่แล้ว (Bridge + Gateway ต่อกันแล้ว)\n\n**1. Hook (`~/.hermes/hooks/minimax-bridge/handler.py`)** — รันบน `agent:start` event\n- ถ้า bridge สำเร็จ → set `context[\"_bridge_done\"] = True` + `context[\"_bridge_result\"] = <result>`\n- ถ้า bridge fail → ไม่ทำอะไร เป็น default\n\n**2. Gateway (`gateway/run.py` lines 6406-6426)** — ตรวจสอบหลัง hook รัน:\n```python\nif hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_done\") and hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_result\"):\n    response = hook_ctx[\"_bridge_result\"]\n    # skip agent, return result directly\nelse:\n    # run agent normally\n```\n\n**สรุป:** Bridge hook → Gateway check → ถ้า `_bridge_done` → skip agent ✅\n\n---\n\n### ❓ ยังไม่ชัด — ช่วยชี้แจนเพิ่ม\n\nเจ้านายบอก \"agent ยังไม่รู้จัก `_bridge_done` flag\"\n\n**ผมเข้าใจว่ามี 2 กรณี:**\n\n**กรณี A:** Agent ยังต้องทำงาน (bridge ไม่สำเร็จ) แต่ agent ไม่รู้ว่า bridge พยายามทำอะไร → **agent ไม่มี context ว่า bridge คืออะไร**\n\n**กรณี B:** Agent run แล้ว แต่ไม่ respect `_bridge_done` flag ที่ hook set ไว้ → **gateway ส่ง flag ไปให้ agent ด้วย**\n\n---\n\n**ช่วยบอกว่าเจ้านายหมายถึงกรณีไหน?** แล้วบอกด้วยว่าต้องการให้ agent รู้เพื่ออะไร — เช่น:\n- Agent ต้องรู้ว่า message นี้ผ่าน bridge มาแล้ว ต้องใช้ result แทน\n- Agent ต้องรู้ว่า bridge ล้ม ต้อง fallback\n- อื่น ๆ\n\nรอเจ้านายชี้แจนก่อนครับ 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":516,"output":1190,"cacheRead":117312,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119018,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778319598429,"responseId":"064e33f0f1d39f8b2b58959e14787096"}}
