{"type":"message","id":"321e5517","parentId":"21e68ff4","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:42:22.615Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying the 4-UNIT BRIDGE system is broken - it outputs a report instead of actually running the task. They're saying they want to call a skill in Hermes but when they embed it in the \"field\" (config), it shows this report output instead of working properly.\n\nLet me understand the issue:\n1. The user has a 4-UNIT bridge system (universal_bridge.py) that routes through MiniMax\n2. When they call it through the hook (agent:start), it works but outputs a report instead of the actual result\n3. They want the skill to be called in Hermes every time they start using it\n4. When they embed it in the \"field\" (likely config/gateway), it shows this broken output\n\nThe problem seems to be:\n- The hook sets `_bridge_done = True` and `_bridge_result` \n- But the `_bridge_result` contains the full 4-UNIT report instead of just the final result\n- The gateway skips the agent when `_bridge_done` is True, but returns `_bridge_result` which is the ENTIRE report\n\nThe user wants the flow to be:\n1. Hook fires\n2. Bridge runs → gets actual result\n3. Returns just the result, not a report\n\nBut currently what's happening:\n- Hook sets `_bridge_done = True`\n- Gateway returns `_bridge_result` which is the full 4-UNIT report text\n\nThe fix needed:\n1. The hook's `_bridge_result` should contain ONLY the final answer, not the whole report\n2. OR the bridge script should be called differently to get just the result\n\nBut wait - the user said \"when I embed it in the field it shows like this\" - meaning the minimax-bridge hook is embedded in the config but it's showing the full report output instead of working.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the user's message: \"ทั้งที่ถามไปมันจะตอบมาแบบนี้หมดเลย\" (everything gets answered like this) - meaning ANY question gets the 4-UNIT bridge report instead of an actual answer.\n\n\nThe core issue is that the gateway isn't respecting `_bridge_done` when it should be, so the full report gets returned instead of just the result. The user wants to call a Hermes skill every time they start using the system, but the current setup causes the bridge report to display instead of the actual skill output. I need to find where the gateway checks `_bridge_done` and ensure it's properly returning just the result rather than the entire report.\n","thinkingSignature":"fb67b8d3c3a9a86c078097b59d938448bfc07f1139120ee8fd5c867f9322f755"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r7255st1b0ci_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '6400,6450p' ~/.hermes/hermes-agent/gateway/run.py","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r7255st1b0ci_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"_bridge_result\\|_bridge_done\" ~/.hermes/hermes-agent/gateway/run.py | head -20","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10737,"output":643,"cacheRead":108544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119924,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778319716577,"responseId":"064e34699e3c0421884bcbd55790eb09"}}
{"type":"message","id":"dcbff770","parentId":"321e5517","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:42:22.743Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r7255st1b0ci_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"self.adapters.get(source.platform),\n            session_key,\n            run_generation,\n        )\n\n        try:\n            # Emit agent:start hook (minimax-bridge hook sets _bridge_done if message should go through bridge)\n            hook_ctx = {\n                \"platform\": source.platform.value if source.platform else \"\",\n                \"user_id\": source.user_id,\n                \"session_id\": session_entry.session_id,\n                \"message\": message_text[:500],\n            }\n            await self.hooks.emit(\"agent:start\", hook_ctx)\n\n            # If bridge hook set _bridge_done → skip agent, return bridge result directly\n            if hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_done\") and hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_result\"):\n                response = hook_ctx[\"_bridge_result\"]\n                agent_result = {\"final_response\": response, \"messages\": [], \"api_calls\": 0}\n            else:\n                # Run the agent normally\n                agent_result = await self._run_agent(\n                    message=message_text,\n                    context_prompt=context_prompt,\n                    history=history,\n                    source=source,\n                    session_id=session_entry.session_id,\n                    session_key=session_key,\n                    run_generation=run_generation,\n                    event_message_id=event.message_id,\n                    channel_prompt=event.channel_prompt,\n                )\n\n            # Stop persistent typing indicator now that the agent is done\n            try:\n                _typing_adapter = self.adapters.get(source.platform)\n                if _typing_adapter and hasattr(_typing_adapter, \"stop_typing\"):\n                    await _typing_adapter.stop_typing(source.chat_id)\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n\n            if not self._is_session_run_current(_quick_key, run_generation):\n                logger.info(\n                    \"Discarding stale agent result for %s — generation %d is no longer current\",\n                    _quick_key or \"?\",\n                    run_generation,\n                )\n                _stale_adapter = self.adapters.get(source.platform)\n                if getattr(type(_stale_adapter), \"pop_post_delivery_callback\", None) is not None:\n                    _stale_adapter.pop_post_delivery_callback(\n                        _quick_key,"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":112,"aggregated":"self.adapters.get(source.platform),\n            session_key,\n            run_generation,\n        )\n\n        try:\n            # Emit agent:start hook (minimax-bridge hook sets _bridge_done if message should go through bridge)\n            hook_ctx = {\n                \"platform\": source.platform.value if source.platform else \"\",\n                \"user_id\": source.user_id,\n                \"session_id\": session_entry.session_id,\n                \"message\": message_text[:500],\n            }\n            await self.hooks.emit(\"agent:start\", hook_ctx)\n\n            # If bridge hook set _bridge_done → skip agent, return bridge result directly\n            if hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_done\") and hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_result\"):\n                response = hook_ctx[\"_bridge_result\"]\n                agent_result = {\"final_response\": response, \"messages\": [], \"api_calls\": 0}\n            else:\n                # Run the agent normally\n                agent_result = await self._run_agent(\n                    message=message_text,\n                    context_prompt=context_prompt,\n                    history=history,\n                    source=source,\n                    session_id=session_entry.session_id,\n                  