{"type":"message","id":"615ffc5c","parentId":"74919ce0","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:42:52.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the gateway logic. The hook fires and sets `_bridge_done` and `_bridge_result`. Then the gateway checks these and either skips agent or runs agent.\n\nBut the user is seeing the 4-UNIT BRIDGE output as the final response. This means the gateway IS getting the bridge result and returning it. But the problem is: the 4-UNIT BRIDGE output is being shown as the final response to the user, not just the final result.\n\nThe issue seems to be that the bridge is outputting a multi-stage progress report as its response, rather than just the final result. The 4-UNIT BRIDGE text includes all the stage outputs (UNIT 1, 2, 3, 4, etc.) and the final report.\n \nSo the real problem is that `universal_bridge.py` is outputting these ANSI progress logs and the final report as its response, when it should only be returning the actual result. The output needs to be stripped of all the stage progress information and just give me the final result, then the gateway can return that cleanly to the user.\n\nLooking at how the hook processes this, it just takes `proc.stdout.strip()` and puts it directly into `_bridge_result`, so everything the script prints—including all those stage logs—gets sent back as the response. I need to either modify the script to suppress the progress output and only print the final result, or modify the hook to extract only the actual result from the output.\n","thinkingSignature":"e4687073bc564b3a0b4a3ded71809ccac653204a5622bb0292a127544987bc7c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mibej76zjr5h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -30 ~/.hermes/hooks/minimax-bridge/handler.py","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mibej76zjr5h_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -30 ~/.hermes/logs/gateway.log | grep -v \"^{\" | head -15","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":687,"output":397,"cacheRead":119232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120316,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778319742749,"responseId":"064e3481a6bddf0e11a76ef61cb92dc6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba5cbb2e","parentId":"615ffc5c","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:42:52.150Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mibej76zjr5h_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nMinimax Bridge Preprocessor Hook\n\nFires on: agent:start\nPurpose:  ทุกข้อความจากเจ้านาย ต้องผ่าน universal_bridge.py ก่อน\n          ถ้า bridge สำเร็จ → inject ผลลัพธ์ลง context แล้ว agent จบทันที\n          ถ้า bridge ล้ม → ปล่อย agent ประมวลผลตามปกติ\n\nContext modified:\n  - _bridge_result: str   — ผลลัพธ์จาก bridge (ถ้าสำเร็จ)\n  - _bridge_done: bool   — True = บอก agent ว่าจบแล้ว ไม่ต้องทำอะไร\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport uuid\nimport os\nimport tempfile\n\nSCRIPT_PATH = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.hermes/scripts/universal_bridge.py\")\nALLOWED_USER = \"robberzaz\"  # Telegram username ของเจ้านาย\n\n\ndef handle(event_type: str, context: dict) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Run on agent:start. Pipe message through bridge, inject result or pass through.\"\"\"\n    if event_type != \"agent:start\":\n        return\n\n    message: str = context.get(\"message\", \"\") or \"\"\n    platform: str = context.get(\"platform\", \"\") or \"\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"\"\"\"\nMinimax Bridge Preprocessor Hook\n\nFires on: agent:start\nPurpose:  ทุกข้อความจากเจ้านาย ต้องผ่าน universal_bridge.py ก่อน\n          ถ้า bridge สำเร็จ → inject ผลลัพธ์ลง context แล้ว agent จบทันที\n          ถ้า bridge ล้ม → ปล่อย agent ประมวลผลตามปกติ\n\nContext modified:\n  - _bridge_result: str   — ผลลัพธ์จาก bridge (ถ้าสำเร็จ)\n  - _bridge_done: bool   — True = บอก agent ว่าจบแล้ว ไม่ต้องทำอะไร\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport uuid\nimport os\nimport tempfile\n\nSCRIPT_PATH = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.hermes/scripts/universal_bridge.py\")\nALLOWED_USER = \"robberzaz\"  # Telegram username ของเจ้านาย\n\n\ndef handle(event_type: str, context: dict) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Run on agent:start. Pipe message through bridge, inject result or pass through.\"\"\"\n    if event_type != \"agent:start\":\n        return\n\n    message: str = context.get(\"message\", \"\") or \"\"\n    platform: str = context.get(\"platform\", \"\") or \"\"","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778319772150}}
