2026-05-09 16:15:43,118 INFO gateway.run: 2 hook(s) loaded\n2026-05-09 16:29:09,434 INFO gateway.run: response ready: platform=telegram chat=1060942816 time=81.4s api_calls=0 response=1112 chars\n2026-05-09 16:29:10,155 INFO gateway.platforms.base: [Telegram] Sending response (1112 chars) to 1060942816\n2026-05-09 16:33:04,686 INFO gateway.run: response ready: platform=telegram chat=1060942816 time=79.8s api_calls=0 response=1116 chars\n2026-05-09 16:33:05,039 INFO gateway.platforms.base: [Telegram] Sending response (1116 chars) to 1060942816\n2026-05-09 16:33:17,559 INFO gateway.platforms.base: [Telegram] Sending response (119 chars) to 1060942816\n2026-05-09 16:34:22,077 INFO gateway.run: 2 hook(s) loaded\n2026-05-09 16:34:35,240 INFO gateway.platforms.base: [Telegram] Sending response (281 chars) to 1060942816\n2026-05-09 16:34:47,189 INFO gateway.run: response ready: platform=telegram chat=1060942816 time=4.4s api_calls=0 response=1061 chars\n2026-05-09 16:34:47,335 INFO gateway.platforms.base: [Telegram] Sending response (1061 chars) to 1060942816\n2026-05-09 16:35:21,282 INFO gateway.run: response ready: platform=telegram chat=1060942816 time=17.2s api_calls=0 response=1070 chars\n2026-05-09 16:35:21,344 INFO gateway.platforms.base: [Telegram] Sending response (1070 chars) to 1060942816","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778319827664}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b9e300f","parentId":"349a5841","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:44:19.758Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the real issue clearly. Let me trace the problem:\n\n1. **The skill** `minimax-workflow/SKILL.md` says:\n   - \"ทุกข้อความจากเจ้านาย → ต้องเรียก workflow นี้ก่อนเสมอ\"\n   - รัน: `python ~/.hermes/scripts/universal_bridge.py \"<task>\"`\n   \n2. **The hook** `minimax-bridge/handler.py` runs `universal_bridge.py` and sets `_bridge_done` + `_bridge_result` on success. But the skill is loaded separately.\n\n3. **The gateway** checks `_bridge_done` and skips the agent if it's set.\n\n4. **The problem:** When the gateway calls `agent:start` hook, the hook runs `universal_bridge.py` as a subprocess and captures its stdout (which is the 4-UNIT BRIDGE report format). But this report is being sent directly back to Telegram, NOT the actual result.\n\nThe hook code does:\n```python\nif proc.returncode == 0:\n    result = proc.stdout.strip()\n    if result:\n        context[\"_bridge_result\"] = result\n        context[\"_bridge_done\"] = True\n```\n\nSo `_bridge_result` gets the raw stdout of the script, which is the whole 4-UNIT BRIDGE report (📊 FINAL REPORT, etc.), not just the actual response to the user's question.\n\n**The fundamental issue is:**\n\n1. Hook fires on `agent:start` → runs `universal_bridge.py` → gets full report output → sets as `_bridge_result`\n2. Gateway sees `_bridge_done` → skips agent → returns `_bridge_result` directly\n3. But `_bridge_result` = the entire 4-UNIT BRIDGE report format (with colored headers, units, etc.)\n\n\n4. Instead of a clean user-facing response, the user sees the whole bridge machinery.\n\nThe hook isn't parsing the actual answer from the script's output—it's just dumping the entire formatted report back to Telegram. So when the user says \"ชื่อไน\", they're getting the entire 4-UNIT BRIDGE debug output instead of just \"ชื่อไน\". The hook needs to extract the actual response, not the full report format.\n\nAdditionally, the 4-UNIT BRIDGE appears to be running twice—once through the hook and again when the agent starts and loads the skill. This duplication means the report is being generated and displayed even when it shouldn't be.\n","thinkingSignature":"71b911d9788ebe570ab0523e42f9e3fd206bd51bf859d555b1052997aabe4510"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rh03eu6sh0lv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -200 ~/.hermes/logs/gateway.log | grep -v \"^{\" | grep -E \"hook|bridge|preflight\" | head -20","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rh03eu6sh0lv_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"preflight_codework_gate\" ~/.hermes/hooks/ -r 2>/dev/null | head -10","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rh03eu6sh0lv_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.hermes/hooks/preflight_codework_gate/handler.py 2>/dev/null | head -50","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2290,"output":713,"cacheRead":122240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125243,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778319827670,"responseId":"064e34d5cba02ddbf47e9fc178fca3d1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a3c191b3","parentId":"2b9e300f","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:44:19.832Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rh03eu6sh0lv_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2026-05-09 14:31:33,721 INFO gateway.run: 1 hook(s) loaded\n2026-05-09 16:15:43,118 INFO gateway.run: 2 hook(s) loaded\n2026-05-09 16:34:22,077 INFO gateway.run: 2 hook(s) loaded"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":36,"aggregated":"2026-05-09 14:31:33,721 INFO gateway.run: 1 hook(s) loaded\n2026-05-09 16:15:43,118 INFO gateway.run: 2 hook(s) loaded\n2026-05-09 16:34:22,077 INFO gateway.run: 2 hook(s) loaded","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778319859832}}
{"type":"message","id":"ac633ccc","parentId":"a3c191b3","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:44:19.832Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rh03eu6sh0lv_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/apinan/.hermes/hooks/preflight_codework_gate/HOOK.yaml:1:name: preflight_codework_gate"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":33,"aggregated":"/home/apinan/.hermes/hooks/preflight_codework_gate/HOOK.yaml:1:name: preflight_codework_gate","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778319859832}}
{"type":"message","id":"729983c2","parentId":"ac633ccc","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:44:19.833Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rh03eu6sh0lv_3","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nPreflight Codework Gate Hook\n\nFires on: agent:start\nPurpose:  Check if the incoming task is code/software/automation work.\n          If yes, force socraticode-codework-gate routing before agent processes it.\n\nContext received:\n  - message (str): the user's raw message\n  - platform (str): messaging platform (telegram, discord, etc.)\n  - chat_id (str): chat identifier\n\nWhat this hook does:\n  1. Extract user message from context\n  2. Classify via lightweight keyword check (fast path — no LLM needed)\n  3. If likely codework, inject a reminder into context to ensure socraticode routing\n  4. The main agent loop will see the flag and call socraticode-codework-gate first\n\nThe actual SocratiCode call MUST still happen in the agent loop — this hook\nonly ensures the gate is NOT skipped by adding a强制 flag to context.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport re\n\n# Keywords that strongly indicate code/software/automation work\n_CODEWORK_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"\\b(โค้ด|code|script|สคริปต์|terminal|powershell|bash|python|js|ts|api|config|patch|build|run|exec|cmd)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(แก้|debug|บั๊ก|error|bug|fix|ไฟล์|file|โปรเจกต์|project|repo|git|docker|ci|cd)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(automation|automate|playwright|selenium|ufo|chrome|cdp|browser|browser_)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(skill|สกิล|hermes|gateway|hook|mcp|ollama|model|provider)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(generate_bg|gpt_image|start_chrome|verify_cdp|comfyui|workflow)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(linux|wsl|windows|systemd|service|process|daemon)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(memory|socrati|socraticode|codebase|index|search_files|read_file|patch)\\b\",\n    r\"^[\\/\\$](\\w+)\",  # slash or dollar commands\n]\n\n_CODEWORK_RE = re.compile(\"|\".join(_CODEWORK_PATTERNS), re.IGNORECASE)\n\n# Keywords that indicate creative/media only — NOT codework\n_NON_CODEWORK_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"^(สร้างรูป|สร้าง|generate|image|รูป|picture|photo)\\s\",\n    r\"^(วาด|draw|paint|art|งานศิลปะ)\\s\",\n    r\"^(แปล|translate|สรุป|summarize|เขียน|write)\\s\",\n]\n_NON_CODEWORK_RE = re.compile(\"|\".join(_NON_CODEWORK_PATTERNS), re.IGNORECASE)\n\n# URL/file paths that are clearly code inspection\n_INSPECTION_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"/\\w+\\.(py|js|ts|ps1|sh|yaml|yml|json|md|txt|toml|cfg|conf|ini)$\",\n    r\"^~/\\.hermes/\","}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":52,"aggregated":"\"\"\"\nPreflight Codework Gate Hook\n\nFires on: agent:start\nPurpose:  Check if the incoming task is code/software/automation work.\n          If yes, force socraticode-codework-gate routing before agent processes it.\n\nContext received:\n  - message (str): the user's raw message\n  - platform (str): messaging platform (telegram, discord, etc.)\n  - chat_id (str): chat identifier\n\nWhat this hook does:\n  1. Extract user message from context\n  2. Classify via lightweight keyword check (fast path — no LLM needed)\n  3. If likely codework, inject a reminder into context to ensure socraticode routing\n  4. The main agent loop will see the flag and call socraticode-codework-gate first\n\nThe actual SocratiCode call MUST still happen in the agent loop — this hook\nonly ensures the gate is NOT skipped by adding a强制 flag to context.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport re\n\n# Keywords that strongly indicate code/software/automation work\n_CODEWORK_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"\\b(โค้ด|code|script|สคริปต์|terminal|powershell|bash|python|js|ts|api|config|patch|build|run|exec|cmd)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(แก้|debug|บั๊ก|error|bug|fix|ไฟล์|file|โปรเจกต์|project|repo|git|docker|ci|cd)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(automation|automate|playwright|selenium|ufo|chrome|cdp|browser|browser_)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(skill|สกิล|hermes|gateway|hook|mcp|ollama|model|provider)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(generate_bg|gpt_image|start_chrome|verify_cdp|comfyui|workflow)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(linux|wsl|windows|systemd|service|process|daemon)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(memory|socrati|socraticode|codebase|index|search_files|read_file|patch)\\b\",\n    r\"^[\\/\\$](\\w+)\",  # slash or dollar commands\n]\n\n_CODEWORK_RE = re.compile(\"|\".join(_CODEWORK_PATTERNS), re.IGNORECASE)\n\n# Keywords that indicate creative/media only — NOT codework\n_NON_CODEWORK_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"^(สร้างรูป|สร้าง|generate|image|รูป|picture|photo)\\s\",\n    r\"^(วาด|draw|paint|art|งานศิลปะ)\\s\",\n    r\"^(แปล|translate|สรุป|summarize|เขียน|write)\\s\",\n]\n_NON_CODEWORK_RE = re.compile(\"|\".join(_NON_CODEWORK_PATTERNS), re.IGNORECASE)\n\n# URL/file paths that are clearly code inspection\n_INSPECTION_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"/\\w+\\.(py|js|ts|ps1|sh|yaml|yml|json|md|txt|toml|cfg|conf|ini)$\",\n    r\"^~/\\.hermes/\",","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778319859832}}
{"type":"message","id":"0c85844d","parentId":"729983c2","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:44:36.210Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see. The preflight_codework_gate hook fires on agent:start and checks if the message is codework, then injects a flag. But the hook doesn't respect _bridge_done from minimax-bridge. They could be racing for the same event.\n\nLet me check the full preflight hook handler.\n","thinkingSignature":"4a848e48871631771f05e3fb22910f13d4d6ee175682dc99fb557cb7b4392b69"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_388tu6jb304m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.hermes/hooks/preflight_codework_gate/handler.py 2>/dev/null","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1054,"output":117,"cacheRead":124480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125651,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778319859841,"responseId":"064e34f53b1f9b0d15defca8c0c69b66"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b6e5e181","parentId":"0c85844d","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:44:36.254Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_388tu6jb304m_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nPreflight Codework Gate Hook\n\nFires on: agent:start\nPurpose:  Check if the incoming task is code/software/automation work.\n          If yes, force socraticode-codework-gate routing before agent processes it.\n\nContext received:\n  - message (str): the user's raw message\n  - platform (str): messaging platform (telegram, discord, etc.)\n  - chat_id (str): chat identifier\n\nWhat this hook does:\n  1. Extract user message from context\n  2. Classify via lightweight keyword check (fast path — no LLM needed)\n  3. If likely codework, inject a reminder into context to ensure socraticode routing\n  4. The main agent loop will see the flag and call socraticode-codework-gate first\n\nThe actual SocratiCode call MUST still happen in the agent loop — this hook\nonly ensures the gate is NOT skipped by adding a强制 flag to context.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport re\n\n# Keywords that strongly indicate code/software/automation work\n_CODEWORK_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"\\b(โค้ด|code|script|สคริปต์|terminal|powershell|bash|python|js|ts|api|config|patch|build|run|exec|cmd)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(แก้|debug|บั๊ก|error|bug|fix|ไฟล์|file|โปรเจกต์|project|repo|git|docker|ci|cd)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(automation|automate|playwright|selenium|ufo|chrome|cdp|browser|browser_)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(skill|สกิล|hermes|gateway|hook|mcp|ollama|model|provider)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(generate_bg|gpt_image|start_chrome|verify_cdp|comfyui|workflow)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(linux|wsl|windows|systemd|service|process|daemon)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(memory|socrati|socraticode|codebase|index|search_files|read_file|patch)\\b\",\n    r\"^[\\/\\$](\\w+)\",  # slash or dollar commands\n]\n\n_CODEWORK_RE = re.compile(\"|\".join(_CODEWORK_PATTERNS), re.IGNORECASE)\n\n# Keywords that indicate creative/media only — NOT codework\n_NON_CODEWORK_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"^(สร้างรูป|สร้าง|generate|image|รูป|picture|photo)\\s\",\n    r\"^(วาด|draw|paint|art|งานศิลปะ)\\s\",\n    r\"^(แปล|translate|สรุป|summarize|เขียน|write)\\s\",\n]\n_NON_CODEWORK_RE = re.compile(\"|\".join(_NON_CODEWORK_PATTERNS), re.IGNORECASE)\n\n# URL/file paths that are clearly code inspection\n_INSPECTION_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"/\\w+\\.(py|js|ts|ps1|sh|yaml|yml|json|md|txt|toml|cfg|conf|ini)$\",\n    r\"^~/\\.hermes/\",\n    r\"^/home/\",\n    r\"^C:\\\\Users\",\n]\n_INSPECTION_RE = re.compile(\"|\".join(_INSPECTION_PATTERNS), re.IGNORECASE)\n\n\ndef handle(event_type: str, context: dict) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Run on agent:start. Sets context flags to enforce socraticode routing.\"\"\"\n    if event_type != \"agent:start\":\n        return\n\n    message: str = context.get(\"message\", \"\") or \"\"\n    message_lower = message.lower().strip()\n\n    # Fast rejection: clearly creative-only tasks\n    if _NON_CODEWORK_RE.match(message_lower):\n        context[\"_codework_gate_passed\"] = True\n        context[\"_codework_routing\"] = \"direct\"  # no gate needed\n        return\n\n    # Check inspection targets (paths in the message)\n    if _INSPECTION_RE.search(message):\n        context[\"_codework_gate_required\"] = True\n        context[\"_codework_routing\"] = \"socraticode\"\n        return\n\n    # Keyword scan for code/software/automation signals\n    if _CODEWORK_RE.search(message):\n        context[\"_codework_gate_required\"] = True\n        context[\"_codework_routing\"] = \"socraticode\"\n        return\n\n    # Default: let agent decide (no forced routing)\n    context[\"_codework_gate_passed\"] = False\n    context[\"_codework_routing\"] = \"agent_discretion\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":20,"aggregated":"\"\"\"\nPreflight Codework Gate Hook\n\nFires on: agent:start\nPurpose:  Check if the incoming task is code/software/automation work.\n          If yes, force socraticode-codework-gate routing before agent processes it.\n\nContext received:\n  - message (str): the user's raw message\n  - platform (str): messaging platform (telegram, discord, etc.)\n  - chat_id (str): chat identifier\n\nWhat this hook does:\n  1. Extract user message from context\n  2. Classify via lightweight keyword check (fast path — no LLM needed)\n  3. If likely codework, inject a reminder into context to ensure socraticode routing\n  4. The main agent loop will see the flag and call socraticode-codework-gate first\n\nThe actual SocratiCode call MUST still happen in the agent loop — this hook\nonly ensures the gate is NOT skipped by adding a强制 flag to context.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport re\n\n# Keywords that strongly indicate code/software/automation work\n_CODEWORK_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"\\b(โค้ด|code|script|สคริปต์|terminal|powershell|bash|python|js|ts|api|config|patch|build|run|exec|cmd)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(แก้|debug|บั๊ก|error|bug|fix|ไฟล์|file|โปรเจกต์|project|repo|git|docker|ci|cd)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(automation|automate|playwright|selenium|ufo|chrome|cdp|browser|browser_)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(skill|สกิล|hermes|gateway|hook|mcp|ollama|model|provider)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(generate_bg|gpt_image|start_chrome|verify_cdp|comfyui|workflow)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(linux|wsl|windows|systemd|service|process|daemon)\\b\",\n    r\"\\b(memory|socrati|socraticode|codebase|index|search_files|read_file|patch)\\b\",\n    r\"^[\\/\\$](\\w+)\",  # slash or dollar commands\n]\n\n_CODEWORK_RE = re.compile(\"|\".join(_CODEWORK_PATTERNS), re.IGNORECASE)\n\n# Keywords that indicate creative/media only — NOT codework\n_NON_CODEWORK_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"^(สร้างรูป|สร้าง|generate|image|รูป|picture|photo)\\s\",\n    r\"^(วาด|draw|paint|art|งานศิลปะ)\\s\",\n    r\"^(แปล|translate|สรุป|summarize|เขียน|write)\\s\",\n]\n_NON_CODEWORK_RE = re.compile(\"|\".join(_NON_CODEWORK_PATTERNS), re.IGNORECASE)\n\n# URL/file paths that are clearly code inspection\n_INSPECTION_PATTERNS = [\n    r\"/\\w+\\.(py|js|ts|ps1|sh|yaml|yml|json|md|txt|toml|cfg|conf|ini)$\",\n    r\"^~/\\.hermes/\",\n    r\"^/home/\",\n    r\"^C:\\\\Users\",\n]\n_INSPECTION_RE = re.compile(\"|\".join(_INSPECTION_PATTERNS), re.IGNORECASE)\n\n\ndef handle(event_type: str, context: dict) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Run on agent:start. Sets context flags to enforce socraticode routing.\"\"\"\n    if event_type != \"agent:start\":\n        return\n\n    message: str = context.get(\"message\", \"\") or \"\"\n    message_lower = message.lower().strip()\n\n    # Fast rejection: clearly creative-only tasks\n    if _NON_CODEWORK_RE.match(message_lower):\n        context[\"_codework_gate_passed\"] = True\n        context[\"_codework_routing\"] = \"direct\"  # no gate needed\n        return\n\n    # Check inspection targets (paths in the message)\n    if _INSPECTION_RE.search(message):\n        context[\"_codework_gate_required\"] = True\n        context[\"_codework_routing\"] = \"socraticode\"\n        return\n\n    # Keyword scan for code/software/automation signals\n    if _CODEWORK_RE.search(message):\n        context[\"_codework_gate_required\"] = True\n        context[\"_codework_routing\"] = \"socraticode\"\n        return\n\n    # Default: let agent decide (no forced routing)\n    context[\"_codework_gate_passed\"] = False\n    context[\"_codework_routing\"] = \"agent_discretion\"","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778319876253}}
{"type":"message","id":"eacb0959","parentId":"b6e5e181","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:45:25.824Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture!\n\nThe problem:\n\n1. **Two hooks fire on `agent:start`:**\n   - `preflight_codework_gate` — sets `_codework_gate_required`, `_codework_routing` flags\n   - `minimax-bridge` — sets `_bridge_done`, `_bridge_result` flags\n\n2. **Both hooks modify the SAME `context` dict** in the same `agent:start` event.\n\n3. **The gateway checks `_bridge_done` at lines 6416-6417** — if true, it skips the agent and returns `_bridge_result` directly.\n\n4. **But the output shown to the user is the 4-UNIT BRIDGE report format** — not a clean response. This means the gateway IS returning the `_bridge_result` (the full 4-UNIT output) as the response!\n   \nThe flow shows that when `_bridge_done` is true and `_bridge_result` contains the 4-UNIT BRIDGE report, the gateway returns this entire report to the user instead of running the agent normally. The bridge script is executing and producing output, but it's returning the full bridge formatting rather than just the final answer. The gateway should skip the agent entirely and just send the bridge result, but instead the full 4-UNIT BRIDGE output is being returned to the user. This suggests either the gateway isn't checking the skip condition properly, or something else is causing the bridge to run again during the agent phase. I'm also noticing the earlier crash event with the timeout issue might be relevant here.\n\nLooking at the actual flow: the \"ชื่อไน\" message received a 17.2s response with 1070 characters and 0 API calls, which matches the full 4-UNIT BRIDGE output rather than a proper agent response. Since `api_calls=0`, the agent wasn't actually invoked—only the bridge ran and returned its raw result, which is why the user saw the complete bridge output instead of a concise answer. Looking at the response sizes and API call counts