d explain why they're seeing the bridge output followed by additional agent processing. the hook sets `_bridge_done`, but then the agent runs anyway and produces its own response. If the bridge result comes back as a 4-UNIT BRIDGE formatted output, that gets injected into context somewhere, and then the agent picks it up and includes it in the final response to the user.\n\nSo the timing issue is that the hook runs first and sets the flag, but the agent still executes afterward and sees the bridge result in context, using it in its response to Telegram. The gateway code clearly shows it should skip the agent when both flags are set, but either the hook isn't properly marking `_bridge_done`, or the agent is running anyway despite what the code says. Looking at the logs, the \"ชื่อไน\" response was 1070 characters and came back in 17.2 seconds, but I need to trace whether the gateway actually respected the bridge result or fell back to running the agent normally. response to Telegram, which matches the 4-UNIT BRIDGE report exactly. So the gateway is returning the full bridge result instead of the concise answer.\n\nThe issue is that the gateway correctly detects `_bridge_done=True` and skips the agent, but it then sends the entire 4-UNIT BRIDGE report as the Telegram response. The user sees this verbose output when they just want \"ชื่อไน\".\n\nI need to check if the bridge script should be returning only the final answer instead of the full report, or if the gateway should be extracting just the answer from the bridge result. I need to extract only the actual answer from the full report that the bridge is returning. The user wants the gateway to pass through just the result without the 4-UNIT diagnostics, so I should modify the gateway logic to strip out the report headers and extract only the meaningful output. the summary/recommendation, and ONLY pass that to Telegram.\n\nOr... the user wants me to understand the FULL picture and propose a fix. Let me just lay it out clearly so the user can tell me what they want.\n\nActually, re-reading the original message more carefully: the user is asking why every response they send gets this 4-UNIT BRIDGE report format. They want every message to go through the workflow as a skill, but when they embed it in the form (gateway/hook), it returns this format instead of just a normal answer.\n\nThe root cause is the gateway's `agent:start` hook calling the bridge and returning the full report as the response instead of just the answer portion.\n\nTo fix this, I need to extract just the summary from the bridge result and return only that. The current code returns the entire `_bridge_result`, which is the full report. I could either modify the bridge to output only the summary, extract the summary from the full result, or ensure only the summary reaches the user.\n\nLet me show the user what I found and ask for their preference on which approach to take.\n","thinkingSignature":"5b350bf1cd51f969214b3f17c4c1991e11f3efb72aa399f207befc47d523bfcc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_go6of2ald1fe_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -500 ~/.hermes/logs/gateway.log | grep -v \"^{\" | grep \"inbound\\|api_calls\\|response ready\" | tail -20","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1107,"output":1495,"cacheRead":125504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128106,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778319876262,"responseId":"064e35070d6c6bf71394a0021b6c51a4"}}
