{"type":"message","id":"d7ef8b10","parentId":"2857b22a","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:45:58.702Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue. Look at these lines:\n\n```\n2026-05-09 16:27:48,000 INFO gateway.run: inbound message: platform=telegram user=▫️ chat=1060942816 msg='แก้ได้ไหม'\n2026-05-09 16:29:09,434 INFO gateway.run: response ready: platform=telegram chat=1060942816 time=81.4s api_calls=0 response=1112 chars\n...\n2026-05-09 16:31:44,891 INFO gateway.run: inbound message: platform=telegram user=▫️ chat=1060942816 msg='เทสระบบ skill'\n\n\n2026-05-09 16:33:04,686 INFO gateway.run: response ready: platform=telegram chat=1060942816 time=79.8s api_calls=0 response=1116 chars\n...\n2026-05-09 16:34:42,811 INFO gateway.run: inbound message: platform=telegram user=▫️ chat=1060942816 msg='ทัก'\n2026-05-09 16:34:47,189 INFO gateway.run: response ready: platform=telegram chat=1060942816 time=4.4s api_calls=0 response=1061 chars\n```\n\nThe pattern is clear: when the user sends \"แก้ได้ไหม\" (can you fix it?) it takes 81 seconds with no API calls and returns 1112 characters, and \"เทสระบบ skill\" (test system skill) takes 79.8 seconds with no API calls and returns 1116 characters. The longer responses with zero API calls suggest the bridge hook is running but the gateway is returning pre-formatted content instead of making actual API calls to process the messages.\n\nWait, I'm realizing the bridge hook might be executing the bridge script which runs the 4-unit pipeline entirely through subprocess calls to MiniMax API and local models, with no gateway API calls involved. The gateway isn't making its own API calls because the hook script is handling the entire pipeline itself.\n\nSo the bridge hook successfully sets `_bridge_done = True` and `_bridge_result` with the full report, and the gateway correctly skips the agent and returns the bridge result directly. This explains why `api_calls=0` — the bridge is handling everything. The gateway only shows `api_calls` from its own agent, not from the hook's subprocess calls.\n\nNow the boss is saying the system is broken — it outputs the 4-UNIT BRIDGE format instead of a normal response. This could mean the gateway isn't routing through the bridge hook properly anymore, perhaps after a restart or reload, causing the agent to process messages without the hook intercepting them first.\n","thinkingSignature":"71ac0332e028498dd48393fe8bee3df47b9a9b320869a78e35a76aa575e0fc45"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9k90j6syn0d4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"reload\\|config change\\|hot.reload\" ~/.hermes/logs/gateway.log 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"^{\" | tail -10","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9k90j6syn0d4_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl --user -u hermes-gateway -n 50 --no-pager 2>&1 | grep -E \"reload|hook|restart|config\" | tail -20","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1269,"output":724,"cacheRead":126592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128585,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778319925872,"responseId":"064e3537f3b393e4762001db2367d8b4"}}
