{"type":"message","id":"89cad1a4","parentId":"6ef68701","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:45:59.281Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9k90j6syn0d4_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"May 09 16:14:59 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S systemd[247]: hermes-gateway.service: Scheduled restart job, restart counter is at 2.\nMay 09 16:15:38 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S python[3015028]: [hooks] Loaded hook 'minimax-bridge' for events: ['agent:start']\nMay 09 16:15:38 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S python[3015028]: [hooks] Loaded hook 'preflight_codework_gate' for events: ['agent:start']\nMay 09 16:33:38 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S systemd[247]: hermes-gateway.service: Scheduled restart job, restart counter is at 3.\nMay 09 16:34:17 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S python[3029968]: [hooks] Loaded hook 'minimax-bridge' for events: ['agent:start']\nMay 09 16:34:17 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S python[3029968]: [hooks] Loaded hook 'preflight_codework_gate' for events: ['agent:start']"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":562,"aggregated":"May 09 16:14:59 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S systemd[247]: hermes-gateway.service: Scheduled restart job, restart counter is at 2.\nMay 09 16:15:38 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S python[3015028]: [hooks] Loaded hook 'minimax-bridge' for events: ['agent:start']\nMay 09 16:15:38 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S python[3015028]: [hooks] Loaded hook 'preflight_codework_gate' for events: ['agent:start']\nMay 09 16:33:38 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S systemd[247]: hermes-gateway.service: Scheduled restart job, restart counter is at 3.\nMay 09 16:34:17 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S python[3029968]: [hooks] Loaded hook 'minimax-bridge' for events: ['agent:start']\nMay 09 16:34:17 DESKTOP-F1PJT4S python[3029968]: [hooks] Loaded hook 'preflight_codework_gate' for events: ['agent:start']","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778319959280}}
{"type":"message","id":"f226b9d5","parentId":"89cad1a4","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:46:16.069Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see it clearly! Both hooks loaded correctly:\n1. `minimax-bridge` - fires on `agent:start`\n2. `preflight_codework_gate` - fires on `agent:start`\n\nBoth are listed in the logs. So the issue is NOT about hooks not being loaded.\n\nNow let me look at what the gateway does after hooks emit. The `api_calls=0` for the messages after the restart is very telling - it means the agent ran but made 0 tool calls, which suggests it just answered from its own knowledge without doing the bridge workflow.\n\nLet me check what the `agent:start` hook context actually contains and what happens after the hooks emit. The key question is: does the gateway check `_bridge_done` BEFORE running the agent, or does the agent itself also need to see the `_bridge_done` flag?\n\nLooking at the gateway code again (lines 6415-6426):\n```python\nif hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_done\") and hook_ctx.get(\"_bridge_result\"):\n    response = hook_ctx[\"_bridge_result\"]\n    agent_result = {\"final_response\": response, \"messages\": [], \"api_calls\": 0}\nelse:\n    # Run the agent normally\n```\n\nSo if `_bridge_done` is True, the gateway skips the agent entirely and returns the bridge result directly. BUT - if the hook doesn't set `_bridge_done` (because bridge failed or timed out or wasn't triggered), then the agent runs normally.\n\nThe problem might be that the hook handler has issues:\n1. The hook checks `if message.startswith(\"_\") or message.startswith(\"/\"): return` - could be skipping legitimate messages\n2. The hook might be failing silently\n3. The script path might be wrong after restart\n\nLet me check the hook handler more carefully and also verify the script path exists.\n","thinkingSignature":"a5d3e62ac9a848899e6cb524db75520c9274ab462911965314bf77506d8719cc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7xg9ck428a2m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.hermes/hooks/minimax-bridge/handler.py","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":463,"output":419,"cacheRead":127808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128690,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778319959284,"responseId":"064e3558be4c82c95bf3d2cb4e1fb42d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f8c79c6","parentId":"f226b9d5","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:46:16.102Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7xg9ck428a2m_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nMinimax Bridge Preprocessor Hook\n\nFires on: agent:start\nPurpose:  ทุกข้อความจากเจ้านาย ต้องผ่าน universal_bridge.py ก่อน\n          ถ้า bridge สำเร็จ → inject ผลลัพธ์ลง context แล้ว agent จบทันที\n          ถ้า bridge ล้ม → ปล่อย agent ประมวลผลตามปกติ\n\nContext modified:\n  - _bridge_result: str   — ผลลัพธ์จาก bridge (ถ้าสำเร็จ)\n  - _bridge_done: bool   — True = บอก agent ว่าจบแล้ว ไม่ต้องทำอะไร\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport uuid\nimport os\nimport tempfile\n\nSCRIPT_PATH = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.hermes/scripts/universal_bridge.py\")\nALLOWED_USER = \"robberzaz\"  # Telegram username ของเจ้านาย\n\n\ndef handle(event_type: str, context: dict) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Run on agent:start. Pipe message through bridge, inject result or pass through.\"\"\"\n    if event_type != \"agent:start\":\n        return\n\n    message: str = context.get(\"message\", \"\") or \"\"\n    platform: str = context.get(\"platform\", \"\") or \"\"\n\n    # ข้ามถ้าเป็น internal/system message\n    if message.startswith(\"_\") or message.startswith(\"/\"):\n        return\n\n    # ข้ามถ้าไม่มี script\n    if not os.path.exists(SCRIPT_PATH):\n        return\n\n    # สร้าง temp file สำหรับ output\n    rid = uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]\n    tmp_out = f\"/tmp/hermes_bridge_{rid}.txt\"\n\n    try:\n        # รัน bridge script\n        cmd = [\"python\", SCRIPT_PATH, message]\n        proc = subprocess.run(\n            cmd,\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n            timeout=120,\n            cwd=os.path.dirname(SCRIPT_PATH),\n        )\n\n        # ถ้าสำเร็จ (exit 0) → inject ผลลัพธ์\n        if proc.returncode == 0:\n            result = proc.stdout.strip()\n            # อ่าน full result จาก stdout\n            if result:\n                context[\"_bridge_result\"] = result\n                context[\"_bridge_done\"] = True\n        # ถ้าไม่สำเร็จ → ปล่อย agent ทำตามปกติ (ไม่ต้องทำอะไร)\n\n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n        context[\"_bridge_timeout\"] = True\n    except Exception as e:\n        context[\"_bridge_error\"] = str(e)\n    finally:\n        # cleanup temp file\n        if os.path.exists(tmp_out):\n            try:\n                os.remove(tmp_out)\n            except Exception:\n                pass"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"\"\"\"\nMinimax Bridge Preprocessor Hook\n\nFires on: agent:start\nPurpose:  ทุกข้อความจากเจ้านาย ต้องผ่าน universal_bridge.py ก่อน\n          ถ้า bridge สำเร็จ → inject ผลลัพธ์ลง context แล้ว agent จบทันที\n          ถ้า bridge ล้ม → ปล่อย agent ประมวลผลตามปกติ\n\nContext modified:\n  - _bridge_result: str   — ผลลัพธ์จาก bridge (ถ้าสำเร็จ)\n  - _bridge_done: bool   — True = บอก agent ว่าจบแล้ว ไม่ต้องทำอะไร\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport uuid\nimport os\nimport tempfile\n\nSCRIPT_PATH = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.hermes/scripts/universal_bridge.py\")\nALLOWED_USER = \"robberzaz\"  # Telegram username ของเจ้านาย\n\n\ndef handle(event_type: str, context: dict) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Run on agent:start. Pipe message through bridge, inject result or pass through.\"\"\"\n    if event_type != \"agent:start\":\n        return\n\n    message: str = context.get(\"message\", \"\") or \"\"\n    platform: str = context.get(\"platform\", \"\") or \"\"\n\n    # ข้ามถ้าเป็น internal/system message\n    if message.startswith(\"_\") or message.startswith(\"/\"):\n        return\n\n    # ข้ามถ้าไม่มี script\n    if not os.path.exists(SCRIPT_PATH):\n        return\n\n    # สร้าง temp file สำหรับ output\n    rid = uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]\n    tmp_out = f\"/tmp/hermes_bridge_{rid}.txt\"\n\n    try:\n        # รัน bridge script\n        cmd = [\"python\", SCRIPT_PATH, message]\n        proc = subprocess.run(\n            cmd,\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n            timeout=120,\n            cwd=os.path.dirname(SCRIPT_PATH),\n        )\n\n        # ถ้าสำเร็จ (exit 0) → inject ผลลัพธ์\n        if proc.returncode == 0:\n            result = proc.stdout.strip()\n            # อ่าน full result จาก stdout\n            if result:\n                context[\"_bridge_result\"] = result\n                context[\"_bridge_done\"] = True\n        # ถ้าไม่สำเร็จ → ปล่อย agent ทำตามปกติ (ไม่ต้องทำอะไร)\n\n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n        context[\"_bridge_timeout\"] = True\n    except Exception as e:\n        context[\"_bridge_error\"] = str(e)\n    finally:\n        # cleanup temp file\n        if os.path.exists(tmp_out):\n            try:\n                os.remove(tmp_out)\n            except Exception:\n                pass","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778319976101}}
{"type":"message","id":"60315909","parentId":"9f8c79c6","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:48:15.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem now. The hook reads `proc.stdout.strip()` and only uses that. But looking at the 4-UNIT BRIDGE output, the actual useful output (the \"Final Report\" summary) is just `✅ สำเร็จแล้ว` - a tiny summary, not the full bridge output.\n\nThe bridge script outputs a LOT of text to stdout (the entire 4-UNIT report). The hook takes `proc.stdout.strip()` which would be the ENTIRE output - including all the ASCII art headers, unit statuses, etc.\n\nBut the gateway just checks if `_bridge_done` is True and `_bridge_result` exists. If both are true, it uses `_bridge_result` directly as the response and SKIPS the agent.\n \nThe user's issue is that when the 4-UNIT bridge ran on \"ชื่อไน\", it produced all that verbose output with the headers and status blocks, and the gateway sent that entire thing back to Telegram instead of running the agent normally. So the user is seeing this massive formatted report rather than a proper response.\n\nLooking at the gateway code, when `_bridge_done` is True and `_bridge_result` exists, it skips the agent entirely and returns the bridge output directly as the final response. That's what's happening here.\n\nThe problem seems to be that even though the user has the hook configured to trigger the bridge, something in the flow is allowing the verbose bridge output to go straight to Telegram rather than being filtered or processed. The user mentioned that previously when the bridge was embedded in the skill itself, it showed this format, but now that it's in the hook, it's not working as expected. I'm looking at what `universal_bridge.py` actually outputs when it succeeds—it should be just the summary in `✅ สำเร็จแล้ว`, but the user is seeing the full 4-UNIT report instead. This makes me think either the bridge is returning the entire report as stdout despite having a