{"type":"message","id":"e2a166fd","parentId":"77ccbff7","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:58:28.123Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants the bridge to work properly - meaning all 4 units should execute properly for every message, and the final answer should come from unit 4's summary. But right now what's happening is:\n\n1. The hook runs the bridge\n2. The bridge outputs a full 4-UNIT report (which includes internal details like \"🟢 UNIT 1\", \"🔵 UNIT 2\", etc.)\n3. The hook takes this full output and puts it in `_bridge_result`\n4. Gateway sees `_bridge_done=True` and skips the agent, returning the full 4-UNIT report to the user\n\nThe user WANTS the 4 units to work - but wants the FINAL OUTPUT to be the UNIT 4 summary (just \"✅ สำเร็จ\" or similar), not the whole 4-UNIT debug report.\n\nSo the fix is:\n1. The hook should still run the bridge (all 4 units execute)\n2. But instead of putting the full stdout into `_bridge_result`, it should extract only the FINAL REPORT / Summary section from the bridge output\n3. The gateway should still skip the agent and return just the summary\n\nLet me look at what the bridge script outputs to understand what we need to extract.\n","thinkingSignature":"acae58ca122aebeeb42482e282690d6706b111610a24c8e2ed5c1999231d98e6"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nเข้าใจแล้วครับ! ต้องการให้:\n- **UNIT 1-4 ทำงานเต็มๆ** (แปล → Plan → Execute → Report)\n- แต่ **ส่งกลับแค่ UNIT 4 Summary** ไม่ใช่ 4-UNIT Report ทั้งด้าม\n\nเดี๋ยวเช็ค bridge script output ก่อนครับว่า summary อยู่ตรงไหน:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tdu15xog77t8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -30 ~/.hermes/scripts/universal_bridge.py | grep -n \"FINAL REPORT\\|Summary\\|══════════\" | head -10","timeout":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tdu15xog77t8_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"def summarize\\|FINAL REPORT\\|Report\\|Summary\" ~/.hermes/scripts/universal_bridge.py | head -20","timeo