{"type":"message","id":"216689e3","parentId":"1b39877a","timestamp":"2026-05-09T09:58:46.541Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_k4pdty2axfkt_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"print(\"═\" * 50)\n    print(\"📋  FINAL REPORT\")\n    print(\"═\" * 50)\n    models = bridge.models\n    print(f\"🟢 {models['translator']}\")\n    print(f\"🔵 {models['architect']}\")\n    print(f\"🟡 {models['coder']}\")\n    print(f\"🟣 {models['reporter']}\")\n    print(f\"🎯 MCP: {', '.join(result['selected_mcp'])}\")\n    print(f\"🔧 Ops: {result['execution']['commands_run']}\")\n    print(f\"📝 Summary:\\n   {result['summary']}\")\n    print(f\"🗑️  Clean: ✅\")"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"print(\"═\" * 50)\n    print(\"📋  FINAL REPORT\")\n    print(\"═\" * 50)\n    models = bridge.models\n    print(f\"🟢 {models['translator']}\")\n    print(f\"🔵 {models['architect']}\")\n    print(f\"🟡 {models['coder']}\")\n    print(f\"🟣 {models['reporter']}\")\n    print(f\"🎯 MCP: {', '.join(result['selected_mcp'])}\")\n    print(f\"🔧 Ops: {result['execution']['commands_run']}\")\n    print(f\"📝 Summary:\\n   {result['summary']}\")\n    print(f\"🗑️  Clean: ✅\")","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778320726540}}
{"type":"message","id":"036683a4","parentId":"216689e3","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:00:12.895Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the problem. The `FINAL REPORT` section includes all the unit details PLUS the summary. The user sees all of this.\n\nWhat the user wants:\n- For simple inputs like \"1234\" → the bridge should work but the final answer should just be what makes sense\n- Actually, looking at the user's original complaint: they sent \"ชื่อไน\" (meaning \"what's your name\") and got the full 4-UNIT report instead of \"ชื่อไน\" being answered\n\nWait - actually, the bridge script runs commands through unit 3. For \"1234\", unit 3 might just echo \"1234\". But the FINAL REPORT includes the full execution trace, not just \"1234\".\n \nSo the real issue is that UNIT 3 executes the command and UNIT 4 summarizes the result, but the entire report including all the execution details gets sent back instead of just the answer. For \"1234\", UNIT 3 echoes it and UNIT 4 would summarize that echo, but what actually returns to the user is the full trace. So the flow makes sense now - UNIT 3 executes the command through the bridge script, then UNIT 4 summarizes the result, and the gateway returns that result to the user, with UNIT 1 potentially doing translation if needed.\n\nThe problem is that the FINAL REPORT printed by the bridge script is verbose and includes unnecessary detail that the user sees. The fix would be to have the hook extract just the actual result from `_bridge_result` rather than dumping the entire report, and only show the verbose output in logs for debugging purposes. So the output the user sees is just \"✅ สำเร็จแล้ว\" - the actual answer that matters. For \"1234\", it runs the echo command and returns the same answer, which makes sense.\n\nThe problem is that the bridge is always outputting the same success message regardless of what command was actually run. When the user asks something like \"ชื่อไน\", the bridge runs it as a bash command (which fails), then reports success anyway. That's why the responses feel hollow - there's no actual intelligence or understanding happening, just a success message for whatever bash command was attempted.","thinkingSignature":"b6417595ca33cc8721f4a2b87e3f604fed8471f66fcb6af13e83a2e8b53daba6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vd3dgmveoi08_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '436,470p' ~/.hermes/scripts/universal_bridge.py","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":113820,"output":514,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":34283,"totalTokens":148617,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778320726553,"responseId":"064e385a45e7f414179f715b7a9b43c2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"14ac35bf","parentId":"036683a4","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:00:12.962Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vd3dgmveoi08_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"class Reporter:\n    MODEL = MODEL_REPORTER\n    _name = f\"🟣 MiniMax-M2.7 [Cloud API, Key-Pool Retry]\"\n\n    def summarize(self, req: str, ex: dict, mcp: list = None) -> str:\n        raw = ex.get(\"raw\",\"\")\n        if not raw: return \"ไม่มีผลลัพธ์\"\n        # แค่บอกว่า สำเร็จ/ไม่สำเร็จ สั้นๆ เป็น TH\n        if \"error\" in raw.lower() or \"❌\" in raw:\n            return f\"❌ มีปัญหา ตรวจสอบดูได้เลย\"\n        return f\"✅ สำเร็จแล้ว\"\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# HELPERS\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\ndef _sz(p: Path) -> str:\n    s = p.stat().st_size if p.is_file() else 0\n    if s >= 1e9: return f\"{s/1e9:.1f}GB\"\n    if s >= 1e6: return f\"{s/1e6:.1f}MB\"\n    if s >= 1e3: return f\"{s/1e3:.1f}KB\"\n    return f\"{s}B\"\n\nclass CleanupManager:\n    @staticmethod\n    def wipe():\n        p = Path(BRIDGE_TMP)\n        if p.exists(): shutil.rmtree(p, ignore_errors=True)\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# 4-UNIT BRIDGE — Main Pipeline\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":42,"aggregated":"class Reporter:\n    MODEL = MODEL_REPORTER\n    _name = f\"🟣 MiniMax-M2.7 [Cloud API, Key-Pool Retry]\"\n\n    def summarize(self, req: str, ex: dict, mcp: list = None) -> str:\n        raw = ex.get(\"raw\",\"\")\n        if not raw: return \"ไม่มีผลลัพธ์\"\n        # แค่บอกว่า สำเร็จ/ไม่สำเร็จ สั้นๆ เป็น TH\n        if \"error\" in raw.lower() or \"❌\" in raw:\n            return f\"❌ มีปัญหา ตรวจสอบดูได้เลย\"\n        return f\"✅ สำเร็จแล้ว\"\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# HELPERS\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\ndef _sz(p: Path) -> str:\n    s = p.stat().st_size if p.is_file() else 0\n    if s >= 1e9: return f\"{s/1e9:.1f}GB\"\n    if s >= 1e6: return f\"{s/1e6:.1f}MB\"\n    if s >= 1e3: return f\"{s/1e3:.1f}KB\"\n    return f\"{s}B\"\n\nclass CleanupManager:\n    @staticmethod\n    def wipe():\n        p = Path(BRIDGE_TMP)\n        if p.exists(): shutil.rmtree(p, ignore_errors=True)\n\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# 4-UNIT BRIDGE — Main Pipeline\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778320812962}}
{"type":"message","id":"9d91de09","parentId":"14ac35bf","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:00:45.517Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue. The `Reporter.summarize()` method returns a short string like \"✅ สำเร็จแล้ว\", but the `FINAL REPORT` section in the main script (lines 600-620) prints a full report including all 4 UNIT labels, MCP tools, ops count, and the summary.\n\nThe problem is:\n1. The hook uses `proc.stdout.strip()` which contains the ENTIRE output of the script (including all the headers, UNIT logs, and final report)\n2. The hook doesn't use `Reporter.summarize()` result at all - it just grabs the raw stdout\n\nSo even though `Reporter.summarize()` returns a short string, the script still prints the full report to stdout, and the hook grabs that full stdout.\n\nThe fix should be:\n1. Modify the script to output ONLY the final summary (line 29: `result['summary']`) - not the full report\n2. OR modify the hook to extract only the summary from the output\n\nActually wait - let me look at line 29 more carefully. The summary is printed from `result['summary']` which comes from `Reporter.summarize()`. So the summary itself IS short (\"✅ สำเร็จแล้ว\"). But the rest of the report (UNIT headers, model names, etc.) is also printed.\n\nThe solution is to modify the script so that ONLY the final summary is output, not the full report. Let me check what `result['summary']` contains - it comes from `Reporter.summarize()`.\n\nBut wait - the boss wants the full UNIT flow to run (1 → 2 → 3 → 4), not just skip. The issue is that the full output of all 4 units is being sent back to Telegram instead of just the final summary.\n\nActually, re-reading the conversation: the boss says:\n\"กูอยากให้มันทำงานเต็มเต็มแบบถ้ากูส่งคำถามไปมันก็ต้องทำงานยูนิตที่หนึ่งก่อนแล้วก็ต่อด้วยสองแล้วก็ต่อด้วยสามแล้วก็ต่อด้วยสี่แบบนี้\"\n\n\nThis means the pipeline should execute all 4 units in sequence, but only the final summary should be returned to Telegram - not the full diagnostic output showing each unit's progress. The current script prints everything to stdout, which the hook then sends back, creating that verbose report. The hook's real issue is that it doesn't actually parse the `result['summary']` value - it just dumps all the diagnostic output.\n\nLooking at the hook implementation, it grabs `proc.stdout.strip()` without any logic to extract just the summary portion. The gateway then sends this entire raw output back, resulting in the full UNIT report appearing in Telegram. I need to either have the hook extract only the summary field from stdout, or modify the script to output only that final summary rather than the complete diagnostic output.\n","thinkingSignature":"fadab541908f039a9345abfbb3481ef0df2d4219bb5abb3878d69976ca79fe1c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5ge47g3c58zk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.hermes/hooks/minimax-bridge/handler.py | grep -A 10 \"returncode == 0\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":492,"output":746,"cacheRead":147200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":148438,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778320812974,"responseId":"064e38af8fe32c0f8f8e5843a6ba82af"}}
{"type":"message","id":"aa05f1f6","parentId":"9d91de09","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:00:45.556Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5ge47g3c58zk_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"if proc.returncode == 0:\n            result = proc.stdout.strip()\n            # อ่าน full result จาก stdout\n            if result:\n                context[\"_bridge_result\"] = result\n                context[\"_bridge_done\"] = True\n        # ถ้าไม่สำเร็จ → ปล่อย agent ทำตามปกติ (ไม่ต้องทำอะไร)\n\n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n        context[\"_bridge_timeout\"] = True\n    except Exception as e:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":19,"aggregated":"if proc.returncode == 0:\n            result = proc.stdout.strip()\n            # อ่าน full result จาก stdout\n            if result:\n                context[\"_bridge_result\"] = result\n                context[\"_bridge_done\"] = True\n        # ถ้าไม่สำเร็จ → ปล่อย agent ทำตามปกติ (ไม่ต้องทำอะไร)\n\n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n        context[\"_bridge_timeout\"] = True\n    except Exception as e:","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778320845556}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b0f23c3","parentId":"aa05f1f6","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:01:15.094Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. Hook receives message \"1234\" → runs bridge script\n2. Bridge script runs ALL 4 UNITS and outputs FULL report to stdout\n3. Hook takes ALL stdout as `_bridge_result` and sets `_bridge_done=True`\n4. Gateway sees `_bridge_done=True` → SKIPS AGENT ENTIRELY\n5. Gateway returns the full report to Telegram\n\nThe problem: Gateway skips agent when `_bridge_done=True`. The hook sends the full report as `_bridge_result`, but since the agent is skipped, the user just sees the raw report.\n\nWhat the boss wants: The 4-UNIT pipeline should run, and the agent should THEN respond naturally - not that the agent is skipped.\n\nActually, re-reading the boss's message again: \"กูอยากให้มันทำงานเต็มเต็มแบบถ้ากูส่งคำถามไปมันก็ต้องทำงานยูนิตที่หนึ่งก่อนแล้วก็ต่อด้วยสองแล้วก็ต่อด้วยสามแล้วก็ต่อด้วยสี่แบบนี้\"\n\nThey want the 4-UNIT pipeline to run as the AGENT's thinking process. Not the bridge preprocessor. Not skip the agent.\n\nSo the issue is: The hook runs the bridge BEFORE the agent starts, and sets `_bridge_done=True` which makes the gateway skip the agent entirely. The boss wants the agent to ALSO run - using the 4-UNIT pipeline as its own thinking/working process.\n\nActually wait - let me re-read: \"แต่อยู่อยู่มันก็ตอบอะไรมาไม่รู้กูไม่เข้าใจว่ามันผิดพลาดอะไร\" = \"but then it answers something I don't understand, I don't know what went wrong\"\n\n\nAnd later: \"กูอยากให้มันทำงานเต็มเต็ม\" = \"I want it to work fully\"\n\nThe boss is saying the agent isn't working at all - it just outputs the report. So I need to fix the gateway behavior: when `_bridge_done` is set, it shouldn't skip the agent, but rather run the agent AND use the bridge result as context for the agent to then respond naturally. That way the 4-UNIT pipeline runs as part of the agent's thinking process, not as a separate preprocessor that bypasses the agent entirely.\n\nThe hook is currently running the bridge and setting `_bridge_done=True`, which causes the gateway to skip the agent. Instead, the bridge output should be made available to the agent so it can continue processing and generate a proper response rather than just outputting the raw bridge result.\n","thinkingSignature":"6eb2f66ff25a06232283550c0a2902d3f8a1061f2ed93541f94b9b1ee4eec46f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pwdr9qwuoomu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '6410,6435p' ~/.hermes/hermes-agent/gateway/run.py","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":240,"output":710,"cacheRead":147648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":148598,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778320845564,"responseId":"064e38cf03cae935c247f630805f807a"}}
